From: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sat, 12 Jun 2021 14:37:46 +0200
Subject: qlcnic: Fix an error handling path in 'qlcnic_probe()'
Patch-mainline: v5.13-rc7
Git-commit: cb3376604a676e0302258b01893911bdd7aa5278
References: git-fixes

If an error occurs after a 'pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting()' call, it
must be undone by a corresponding 'pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting()'
call, as already done in the remove function.

Fixes: 451724c821c1 ("qlcnic: aer support")
Signed-off-by: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_main.c
@@ -2708,6 +2708,7 @@ err_out_free_hw_res:
 	kfree(ahw);
 
 err_out_free_res:
+	pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
 	pci_release_regions(pdev);
 
 err_out_disable_pdev:
